-- Swiss, U.S. Close to Tax Agreement, Ambassador Tells Swissinfo
-- B y   K l a u s   W i l l e
-- 2011-12-20T14:56:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-20/swiss-u-s-close-to-tax-agreement-ambassador-tells-swissinfo.html
Switzerland  and the U.S. are
“reasonably close” to reaching an agreement on untaxed assets
held by Americans in Swiss bank accounts, Manuel Sager, the
Swiss ambassador in  Washington , told Swissinfo website.  Sager is confident that a resolution will be reached within
a “reasonable time frame,” the Bern, Switzerland-based website
reported in an  interview  with the ambassador.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Klaus Wille in Zurich at   kwille@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Craig Stirling at   cstirling1@bloomberg.net  